If you have already installed python and necessary modules then please run code as mentioned:

Running Python Script on Ubuntu:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	(1)Open Terminal (ctrl+alt+T)
Go to the Directory where the files are downloaded(Assuming Downloads)
	(2)cd Downloads/ISB_Assignment
Run the script
	(3)python isb_final.py

As soon as the script executes, It creates "8829700_patent_dwd.html(downloaded patent number)" and "ISB_Strat_Assignement_Patent.xlsx"(excel file) as you requested in the same directory.

If you haven't already installed python and the required modules on Ubuntu, Please follow the following steps:

Python Installation on Ubuntu:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Open Terminal and enter the following commands:

First, install dependencies:
	(1)sudo apt-get install build-essential checkinstall
	(2)sudo apt-get install libreadline-gplv2-dev libncursesw5-dev libssl-dev libsqlite3-dev tk-dev libgdbm-dev libc6-dev libbz2-dev

Then download using the following command:
	(3)cd ~/Downloads/
	(4)wget http://python.org/ftp/python/2.7.5/Python-2.7.5.tgz

Extract and go to the dirctory:
	(5)tar -xvf Python-2.7.5.tgz
	(6)cd Python-2.7.5

Install
	(7)./configure
	(8)make
	(9)sudo checkinstall



To run the isb_final code you also need urllib2 and Beautiful Soup modules:

	(1)urllib2 will be automatically installed with python
To install Beautiful Soup module, Open terminal and enter following commands
	(1)sudo apt-get install python-bs4